# -*- mode: snippet -*-
# name: commit
# key: commit
# --
Commit only the currently staged changes. Follow these steps:
1. Run \`git diff --cached\` to see exactly what is staged
2. Analyze the changes to understand their purpose and scope
3. Write a commit message following conventional commit format (type: description)
4. Use types like: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore
5. Keep the subject line under 72 characters
6. Add a body if the change needs explanation of why, not what
7. Do NOT stage additional files - only commit what is already staged
8. Run the commit command and confirm success
